GB Auto Slumps After Report Issued on Egypt Car Sales Decline

-- B y   A h m e d   A .   N a m a t a l l a
-- 
2011-09-27T09:46:53Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-27/gb-auto-slumps-after-report-issued-on-egypt-car-sales-decline.html
GB Auto, the  Middle East ’s biggest
independent car assembler, fell for the sixth time in seven days
on a report local car sales were down compared with last year.  Shares of the Cairo-based company dropped 1.9 percent to 26
Egyptian pounds at 11:10 a.m. in Cairo, heading for the biggest
daily loss in almost a week. That brought the stock’s decline
for this quarter to 15 percent.  Egypt ’s benchmark  EGX 30 Index (EGX30) 
gained 1.3 percent today.  Car sales in Egypt fell 25 percent in August from a year
earlier to 16,396 vehicles, Al Mal newspaper said today, citing
a report by the  Automotive Marketing Information Council . Sales
of locally assembled cars dropped 31 percent in the first eight
months of the year.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ahmed A Namatalla in Cairo at 
 anamatalla@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Maedler at 
 cmaedler@bloomberg.net  